				<li id="16686682" class="cmnt-root" data="8" data-d="1652763433000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578584/Greatshield-Soldier-Ashes" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">17 May 2022 00:57</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16686682" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">My go to summon for any fight that isn&apos;t cheesy.  If you buff them they can tank bosses like Mogh with ease.  Unless the boss is mobile then all 5 will tend to surround and just chain slam bosses/mobs.  They hold aggro with a roar, fire bombs, their melee and shield bashes.  One of these guys ate the entire melee attack chain of Godfrey and Radahn with little problem on NG+1.  If you want to level as a support/healer I would suggest getting this ASAP, they hold aggro so well you can watch for AoE but other than that you can stand next to them as they handle the content, healing as needed.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16686682" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16686682" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>8</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-