				<li id="16677944" class="cmnt-root" data="7" data-d="1652262679000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578584/Greatshield-Soldier-Ashes" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">11 May 2022 05:51</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16677944" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">If youre a ranged build (such as a mage) these are your god tier summon. All a ranged build really needs is aggro control, to keep enemies off of them while they do damage from afar. Need the enemy to stay distracted while you put down terra magica, gulp down a wondrous physick and other buffs then blast them with your kamehameh- sorry, comet azur? These are your guys. They literally bang on their shields to draw aggro, and will tank the **** out of basically anything. <br/><br/>And there are 5 of them, which makes them the ultimate anti-gank summon as well. Having trouble with a boss because its a group? Godskin duo? Valiant gargoyles? Crystalian trio? Etc? No problem. These guys will outnumber all of them, and draw aggro from all of them too, letting you focus them down one by one at your leisure. <br/><br/>Despite this I rarely use them, ironically because its kinda boring. I use them for anti-gank (looking at you, triple crystalians) but otherwise if its just me and one or two opponents then I still prefer Lhutel or Tiche or mimic, depending. Those summons are just more fun/interesting  to play with. But if you just want to min-max and go purely for whats most effective? These guys. Best summon in the game, easy, outside of highly situational fights like Rykard for example, for whom a mimic with a serpent hunter will always be your best bet. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16677944" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16677944" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>7</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16677944"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16677944" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16677944"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
